      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection (SST k-omega) is justified by published literature on rotating blood-contacting devices; hemolysis power-law model constants are sourced from peer-reviewed calibration studies.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence closure was selected based on published benchmark studies of rotating blood pump geometries demonstrating superior near-wall shear stress prediction relative to k-epsilon variants. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model was parameterised using constants from Heuser and Opitz (1980) as validated in the FDA critical path initiative. No contradictions to these model form choices have been observed in the literature reviewed during this assessment, and no failure modes attributable to this model selection have been encountered across the operating conditions evaluated. Model form achieves required level 2."
